{
  "stem": "24814.3",
  "chunk_idx": 16,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "First I was made a commanding officer of a separate medical battalion, and we were going to go on to fight the Japanese, help the Japanese-- help fight the Japanese, in the China Burma India Theater.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were retraining, as much as you could train for China, and since-- since I'm Germany.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then, the big bomb got dropped, so we knew it was over.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So then, I got assigned to an occupation job.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was in charge of civilian venereal disease in southwest Germany.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had to set up 4,000 civilian venereal disease beds in southwest-- go into the bombed-out cities, find beds, find hospitals, round up doctors from the German prisoner war cages, and try and supply them.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was kind of a chaotic job.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I got to visit with the Germans and talk with them a lot.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "What did you learn from that?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And what I learned from that is the-- I don't know if they're the biggest bunch of liars or deniers, or just myopic people in the world.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The attitudes of the Germans, rarely did they feel a lot of guilt about what had happened.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was an attitude to blame everybody else, and especially in the Rhineland.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was the [INAUDIBLE], north of Heidelberg.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You went up to [INAUDIBLE] toward the Rhine.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was known as a hotbed of Nazi political activity in that part of Germany.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Down in Bavaria, there had been resistance.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When we-- we took the city of Munich-- we surrounded Munich, the Third Division took-- but scouts-- our scouts met people from a resistance outfit called the Bavarian Actions Unit, [SPEAKING GERMAN], who came out and said that they were trying to take over the city from the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Bavaria was-- there was more of a resistance.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
